title: October 2 protests in France: Demonstrators feel disheartened but refuse to give up
byline: By Hélène Bekmezian, Philippe Gagnebet (Toulouse, correspondent), Dorian Jullien, Benjamin Keltz (Rennes, correspondent), Aline Leclerc, Claire Mayer (Bordeaux, correspondent), Thibaud Métais, Gilles Rof (Marseille, correspondent), Richard Schittly (Lyon, correspondent) and Florence Traullé (Lille, correspondent)

title: Yohji Yamamoto, the wise warrior of fashion
subhed: For more than four decades, the Japanese fashion designer has continued to surprise with his radical creations. His austere and rebellious style appeals to a new generation of fans, including stars such as Offset, A$AP Rocky and Burna Boy. At 81, the tireless designer will unveil his new women's collection during Paris Fashion Week, on October 3.
